actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A market is a place where buyers and sellers meet to exchange goods or services.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Not necessarily; a market can exist with barter or free exchanges, not just priced transactions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Zero-price markets can lead to exploitation, as they often lack standards and regulation for consumer protection.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Additionally, these markets might also prioritize profit over user experiences, leading to decreased product satisfaction for consumers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This makes me wonder if the value of time can be considered a hidden cost in these exchanges.
